[[File:村国神社 御旅所.JPG|thumb|250px|right|Murakuni no Oyoru burial site]]

'''Murakuni Shrine''' (むらくにじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Kakamigahara|Q641491|qid=Q641491|1=Kakamigahara}}, {{ill|lt=Gifu Prefecture|Q131277|qid=Q131277|1=Gifu Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|lt=shikinaisha|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}. It is regarded as the tutelary shrine of the Kakami area ({{ill|lt=Kakami Village|Q11412364|qid=Q11412364|lt=Kakami district|1=Kakami}}) in Kakamigahara City. It is one of the five {{ill|lt=Kinpeisha|Q119929592|qid=Q119929592|1=Kinpei-sha}} in Kakamigahara.

According to the Engishiki Jinmyōchō, there are two seats of Murakuni Shrine in {{ill|lt=Kakamigōri|Q11412369|qid=Q11412369|1=Kakami district}}, {{ill|lt=Mino Province|Q864156|qid=Q864156|1=Mino Province}} (now Kakamigahara). There are two Murakuni Shrines in Kakami Ogase-chō 3-chōme, and the other Murakuni Shrine (3-85) is only about 150 meters away in a straight line (about 50 meters from the approach entrance). The shrine at 85 is said to be the site of the grave of {{ill|lt=Murakuni no Oyoru|Q6937264|qid=Q6937264|1=Murakuni Oyori}}, and is now an {{ill|lt=otabisho|Q11489117|qid=Q11489117|1=Otabisho}}. In the precinct next to the haiden stands the playhouse {{ill|lt=Murakuniza|Q11523051|qid=Q11523051|1=Murakuni-za}} ('''Kakami no Butai'''), designated as an {{ill|lt=Important Tangible Folk Cultural Property|Q11644858|qid=Q11644858|1=National Important Tangible Folk Cultural Property}}<ref name="murakuniza">{{Cite web|和書|date= |url=http://www.pref.gifu.lg.jp/kyoiku-bunka-sports/bunka-geijutsu/bunkazai-zuroku/yuumin/kakami.html |title=Kakami no Butai |publisher=Gifu Prefecture |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref>.

=== Outline ===
It is one of the five Kinpeisha in Kakamigahara City.

It is said to have been founded in the {{ill|lt=Asuka period|Q210688|qid=Q210688|1=Asuka period}} by the {{ill|lt=Murakuni clan|Q11523054|qid=Q11523054|1=Murakuni Clan}} with {{ill|lt=Ame-no-Hoakari-no-Mikoto|Q10940411|qid=Q10940411|1=Amenohoakari}} and {{ill|lt=Ishikoridome|Q6080112|qid=Q6080112|lt=Miko Ishikoridome-no-Uba-no-Mikoto|1=Ishikori-dome no Mikoto}} as deities. Later, {{ill|lt=Murakuni no Shigamaro|Q11523052|qid=Q11523052|1=Murakuni no Shigamaro}} jointly enshrined {{ill|lt=Murakuni no Oyoru|Q6937264|qid=Q6937264|1=Murakuni Oyori}}. Around {{ill|lt=900|Q23460|qid=Q23460|1=900}} ({{ill|lt=Shōhō|Q1193592|qid=Q1193592|1=Jōhō}} 3), Hakusan Gongen was jointly enshrined.

In {{ill|lt=1877|Q7773|qid=Q7773|1=1877}} ({{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|qid=Q3125096|1=Meiji era}} 10), {{ill|lt=Murakuniza|Q11523051|qid=Q11523051|1=Murakuni-za}} was completed as the venue for the shrine's dedicated plays ({{ill|lt=kabuki|Q199701|qid=Q199701|1=Kabuki}}), and in {{ill|lt=1882|Q7812|qid=Q7812|1=1882}} (Meiji 15) its opening performance (kokerawotoshi) was held.

On September 25, {{ill|lt=1973|Q2477|qid=Q2477|1=1973}} (Shōwa 48), it was designated by the Gifu Prefectural Shrine Association as a prefectural head-attendance designated shrine ({{ill|lt=Kinpeisha|Q119929592|qid=Q119929592|1=Kinpei-sha}}), designation Kin No. 72{{sfn|Kimura|1997|p=77}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* {{ill|lt=Ame-no-Hoakari-no-Mikoto|Q10940411|qid=Q10940411|1=Amenohoakari}}
* {{ill|lt=Ishikoridome|Q6080112|qid=Q6080112|lt=Miko Ishikoridome-no-Uba-no-Mikoto|1=Ishikori-dome no Mikoto}}
* {{ill|lt=Hakusan Gongen|Q11579578|qid=Q11579578|1=Hakusan Gongen}}
* {{ill|lt=Murakuni no Oyoru|Q6937264|qid=Q6937264|1=Murakuni Oyori}}
=== Precinct shrine ===
* Akiba Shrine

=== Annual festival ===
Every year on the second Saturday and Sunday of October, dedicated kabuki is performed as the annual festival of Murakuni Shrine. It is {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=jikai kabuki|1=UNKNOWN}} centered on children.

